Over the next few months you’ll start to see a few changes to the way we look,
talk and write. This is because we know it is our responsibility to make sure
that people understand both the condition and the growing diabetes crisis.
We will be updating our current logo with our new strapline “Know Diabetes.
Fight Diabetes.” This strapline is designed to reflect the importance of
knowledge in understanding and empowering people to take control of the
condition combined with the need to take action and fight, whether that is
fighting the stigma caused by misunderstanding, fighting for better
The new strapline will be introduced alongside a refreshed look for everything
we do.This is to help us stand out from other charities and ensure people
recognise materials from Diabetes UK wherever they are - whether that’s in a
doctor’s waiting room or at a marathon. Alongside this there will be an update
to our tone of voice and personality to help us find a unified way for us to
This won’t be an overnight change, instead we’ll be introducing new materials
over time as they run out or as they need updating so it’s all done in the
most cost efficient and environmentally friendly way. You’ll start to see the
changes from mid-November so please bear with us and don’t think you have to
If you’re unsure, you can speak to your local volunteering team or contact our
Brand team onBrand@diabetes.org.ukwho will be able to help. We will also be
producing new guidelines to help everyone work with the new elements from mid-
Someone is diagnosed with diabetes every two minutes. Your donation can change
